race.comment: Little between the top half dozen. POSITIVE IMAGE (5) is a two-start maiden stretching out in journey this time. Will find this easier than the close-up fourth last time and drawn for a soft run. Will be prominent and expected to go close. SO STAR (7) is also a two-start maiden who placed on debut over 1300m then found the line strongly for sixth last time over six furlongs. Wasn't far from the winner, blinkers added and extra trip a plus. Has upside and worth following up. PARISH PRIEST (4) ran on hard last time to finish runner-up. Has the big claim and expected to feature again. BLACKLIP (1) was fourth two back then not far away last time over 1300m. At his top and among the chances on best figures. TILL QUEEN (14) resumed from a long break with a solid fifth and will strip much fitter.
